Iran’s Supreme Leader, Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, has mocked the rancorous aftermath of election day in the United States, saying that the vote had exposed the reality of America's democracy. According to AFP, the battle for the White House remains undecided over 24 hours after the last polling station closed in the US state of Alaska. Ayatollah Ali Khamenei See Also






